Channel Seven's Sunday Night will tell the story of Ivan Milat's first violent crime and how he escaped prosecution .
He was convicted of butchering seven backpackers between 1989 and 1992 and buried their bodies in the Belanglo State Forest in southern NSW .
The program also puts Mr Milat face-to-face with the 'wrong man' who was jailed for the first time .
'Don't hold yourself responsible,' the program's program says .